heaviest_rainfall.status: Record amounts of rain fell over 31.0 hours today with a total accumulation of 23.86mm.  It fell at 8.3 mm per hour at times and ranked 7th from our records.  47.89mm of rain was recorded as having fallen on 09 November 2025, marking an exceptional 144.8 hour precipitation event.  At times the rain was falling at 24.6mm per hour.

heaviest_rainrate.status: There was a torrential downpour today where the rain reached a maximum intensity of 27.6mm per hour (ranked 2nd in our records).  The storm lasted 2.3 hours and 5.94mm of precipitation fell during that time.  The heaviest rain was recorded on 02 September 2025 with a peak rate of 34.3mm per hour.  The storm lasted 15.0 hours and had a total rainfall of 21.19mm.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 7th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 31.0 hours; it delivered 23.86mm of rain at a maximum rate of 8.3mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 144.8 hours on 09 November 2025 when 47.89mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 24.6mm per hour.
